The All Progressives Congress has said that they have no record of the embattled Governor of Edo state, Godwin Obaseki’s defection. Reacting to Obaseki’s announcement of leaving the APC on Tuesday afternoon, APC’s National Publicity Secretary Mallam Lanre Issa-Onilu said; “We cannot comment at this moment on media reports suggesting the Edo governor or anyone else has left our great party. “The party has no record of the reported defection of Governor Godwin Obaseki from the Progressive party”. Obaseki had informed he was leaving the APC on Tuesday afternoon while leaving the State House. The party disqualified the Governor from seeking re-election on its platform on the ground of “defective qualifications.” Source The All Progressives Congress has said it was yet to be notified of the reported resignation of the Edo State Governor, Godwin Obaseki. National Publicity Secretary of the APC, Mallam Lanre Issa-Onilu, said this in response to inquiries about Obaseki’s resignation. He said, “The party has no record of the… June 16, 2020 In "News" By Deborah Coker (08035927476 Benin - Mr Anselm Ojezua, factional Chairman, All Progressives Congress (APC) in Edo, says he will not be leaving the party with the governor. Ojezua is leading a faction of the APC loyal to Gov. Godwin Obaseki before his resignation on June 16 from the party.… June 16, 2020 In "Politics" Party’s aspirants insists on contesting primariesDeputy Governor Shuaibu may lose out in dealOkowa leads lobby for governor’s defectionDump APC, supporters tell ObasekiAPC NWC upholds disqualification, expels IduorikemwenPetition raises fresh hurdle for Edo governor The planned defection of Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State to the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) is… June 14, 2020 In "Politics"